                    <h2>Challenge: Maintaining Non-Equilibrium at 1 bar</h2>
                    <p>
                        The cold plasma advantage depends on keeping T<sub
                            >e</sub
                        > &gt;&gt; T<sub>g</sub>. Atmospheric pressure fights
                        this.
                    </p>
                    <div
                        style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:1.5em; margin:1.5em auto; max-width:850px; text-align:left;"
                    >
                        <div class="collection-card" style="text-align:left;">
                            <div
                                style="font-size:clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem); font-weight:700; color:#f59e0b; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;"
                            >
                                ~10<sup>9</sup> collisions/s
                            </div>
                            <h3 style="color:#c0c0d0;">
                                Energy bleeds into waste heat
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Every electron-neutral collision transfers
                                kinetic energy into the bulk gas. A large
                                fraction of microwave input heats the gas rather
                                than maintaining high-energy electrons for
                                ionization.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collection-card" style="text-align:left;">
                            <div
                                style="font-size:clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem); font-weight:700; color:#ef4444; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;"
                            >
                                T<sub>g</sub> &rarr; T<sub>e</sub>
                            </div>
                            <h3 style="color:#c0c0d0;">
                                Plasma drifts toward thermal equilibrium
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                As the gas heats beyond 300&deg;C, N<sub>2</sub> begins
                                to dissociate and NO<sub>x</sub> forms &mdash; exactly
                                what the cold plasma was designed to prevent.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr; gap:1em; margin:1em auto; max-width:850px;"
                    >
                        <div
                            style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius:8px; padding:0.8em; text-align:center;"
                        >
                            <p class="small dim">Limit electron density</p>
                            <p class="small" style="color:#c0c0d0;">
                                &darr; ionization yield
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div
                            style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius:8px; padding:0.8em; text-align:center;"
