                                &darr; energy economics
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div
                            style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius:8px; padding:0.8em; text-align:center;"
                        >
                            <p class="small dim">Accept higher T<sub>g</sub></p>
                            <p class="small" style="color:#c0c0d0;">
                                &darr; selectivity + NO<sub>x</sub> risk
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="small dim" style="margin-top:0.8em;">
                        Every option involves a trade-off. This is where the
                        physics gets genuinely difficult.
                    </p>
                    <p
                        style="margin-top:1em; padding:0.5em 1em; border-left:3px solid #ef4444; background:rgba(239,68,68,0.06); border-radius:0 6px 6px 0; display:inline-block;"
